# Datasheet for MetaConvo-50K

Following the framework of Gebru et al., "Datasheets for Datasets"
(Commun. ACM, 2021).

## Motivation

**For what purpose was the dataset created?**
MetaConvo-50K was created to fine-tune the text modality encoder
(RoBERTa-large) of the MEIA Multimodal Perception Module (Section 4.1 of
the paper) on naturalistic metaverse text-chat interactions, and to
calibrate the simulation behaviour of the MultiEthic-V benchmark.

**Who created the dataset?**
Collected by the MEIA research team headed by Remya sree  under institutional ethics approval
**#IRB-2024-0147**.

## Composition

**What do the instances represent?**
Each instance is an anonymised text-chat transcript fragment exchanged
between a user and a virtual agent during a metaverse interaction session.

**How many instances?**
50,000 anonymised interaction transcripts.

**Does the dataset contain all possible instances or a sample?**
A sample, collected during a 6-month data collection window across three
interaction scenario types matching S1/S2/S3 in the paper's MultiEthic-V
benchmark (Section 5.1).

**What data does each instance consist of?**
Raw text transcript (tokenised), session metadata (scenario type,
duration, turn count), and de-identified sentiment labels.

## Collection Process

**How was the data collected?**
Collected from 48 volunteer participants under a research data-access
agreement and platform Terms-of-Service approval (**DSA-2024-118**), as
described in Section 4.1 of the paper.

**Who was involved in the collection process?**
Research staff under IRB-2024-0147 supervision, with informed consent
obtained from all 48 participants prior to data collection.

## Preprocessing/Cleaning/Labeling

All personally identifying content (names, locations, contact information)
was removed using a combination of automated PII-detection and manual
review prior to any use or release.

## Uses

**Has the dataset been used for any tasks already?**
Yes — fine-tuning the RoBERTa-large text encoder for 10 epochs (Section 4.4,
Stage 1 pre-training) and calibrating simulated text-interaction patterns
in the MultiEthic-V benchmark.

**What other tasks could the dataset be used for?**
General research on metaverse text-interaction modelling, conversational
sentiment analysis in immersive environments.

## Distribution

**Will the dataset be distributed to third parties?**
**Raw transcripts are NOT publicly redistributed** due to licensing
constraints in the underlying platform Terms-of-Service agreement
(DSA-2024-118). This is stated explicitly in Section 4.1 of the paper.

**What is released instead?**
1. This datasheet (full collection and consent protocol)
2. Derived 768-dimensional text embeddings (post-RoBERTa, pre-projection),
   which do not permit reconstruction of the original text, released at
   the Zenodo link in the top-level repository README
3. The fine-tuned RoBERTa-large checkpoint itself (see `checkpoints/`)

## Maintenance

**Who maintains the dataset?**
The corresponding author of the paper. Contact via GitHub Issues on this
repository for questions about data provenance or the consent protocol.

## Ethical Considerations

This dataset was collected under IRB-2024-0147. All 48 participants
provided informed consent for their (de-identified) interaction data to
be used in model training and academic publication. No protected
demographic attributes were collected directly; the demographic-cohort
labels used elsewhere in the paper (Section 4.3) are inferred from
behavioural signals, not from data collected in MetaConvo-50K.
